WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  'Abstracon' is a Workbench game played in various game board
sizes; between 3 by 3 spaces up to a maximum of 7 by 7 spaces size.
There is an 'entry', located somewhere at the top of the board and
an 'exit', which is located at the bottom. The idea is to place
tiles that have random or 'abstract' patterns, so they create a
path from entry to exit. The path made must use all available
spaces on each game board.

  Each tile, in addition to having an abstract drawing pattern,
also has two 'notches', indicating where it must connect with
other neighbouring tiles, as well as the entry or the exit spots
of a game board.

 Try to complete each board in the least amount of moves.

  Have fun!

